OL,3,CGovernment Troubles immunity law
OL,4,C'unlawful'
OL,6,FGovernment plans to offer conditional
OL,7,Fimmunities from prosecution for
OL,8,FTroubles-era crimes and shut down
OL,9,Fcivil actions under the controversial
OL,10,Fnew Legacy Act are unlawful, a High
OL,11,FCourt judge ruled today.JMr Justice
OL,12,FColton declared that parts of the
OL,13,Flegislation aimed at dealing with the
OL,14,Fconsequences of the conflict in
OL,15,FNorthern Ireland breach the European
OL,16,FConvention on Human Rights.JHe also
OL,17,Fheld that a block on paying
OL,18,Fcompensation for a miscarriage of
OL,19,Fjustice to men cleared of escaping
OL,20,Ffrom lawful custody during the 1970s
OL,21,Fis legally flawed.
