OL,6,FIn a separate finding, the judge
OL,7,Fconcluded that a truth recovery body
OL,8,Fat the centre of the plans has
OL,9,Fsufficient independence and powers to
OL,10,Feffectively investigate Troubles-
OL,11,Frelated deaths and offences.JThe
OL,12,FNorthern Ireland Troubles (Legacy and
OL,13,FReconciliation) Act, which came into
OL,14,Feffect last September, offers a
OL,15,Fconditional amnesty to those accused
OL,16,Fof crimes during more than 30 years of
OL,17,Fsectarian violence.JIt will also end
OL,18,Ffuture civil litigation and inquests
OL,19,Finto conflict-related deaths not
OL,20,Fcompleted before the cut-off date of
OL,21,FMay 1.JWith victims organisations,
OL,22,Fpolitical parties and the Irish
OL,23,FGovernment united in opposition, a
OL,24,Fraft of judicial review challenges
OL,25,Fwere brought by some of those who
OL,26,Feither lost loved ones or were injured
