OL,6,FLabour suggested one of its central
OL,7,Fpowers "has just been struck down" by
OL,8,Fthe High Court.JShadow Northern
OL,9,FIreland secretary Hilary Benn told the
OL,10,FCommons: "The Government's Legacy Act
OL,11,Fis opposed by victims groups, all of
OL,12,Fthe political parties in Northern
OL,13,FIreland, the Northern Ireland Human
OL,14,FRights Commission and others.J"This
OL,15,Fmorning the Belfast High Court has
OL,16,Ffound that the immunity provisions of
OL,17,Fthe Act are not compliant with
OL,18,Farticles 2 and 3 of the European
OL,19,FConvention on Human Rights.J"Given
OL,20,Fthat immunity has always been
OL,21,Fpresented as the central foundation of
OL,22,Fthe Legacy Act, what do ministers
OL,23,Fintend to do about this judgment and
OL,24,Fhow can the Commission became
OL,25,Foperational when one of its central
OL,26,Fpowers has just been struck down?"
